Street rave of the moment Portable has revealed the inspiration behind his decision to do music. The controversial self-styled ‘wahala musician’ in a tweet said Wizkid’s popular hit song, “Ojuelegba” was the catalyst that propelled him to start doing music. “Wizkid’s Ojuelegba inspired me to start doing music”, he tweeted. However, his revelation sparked a debate on social media as many claimed even though Big Wiz still continues to inspire younger artistes to follow their dreams, he surely isn’t responsible for this one. Some said Portable’s inspiration ought to be Terry G. - Advertisement - While others were more concerned about the person who tweeted noting Portable can’t write such English. NosikeOtito tweeted: “If Wizkid’s Ojuelegba inspired you, how come your music and his has no semblance? Usually, we mirror our inspirations in our craft. How come there’s literally no nexus between yours and Wizkid’s?” fresh.main said: “Even Wizkid know say the guy dey mad.”   I’ve been depressed for two years – Kida Kudz     Collabo with Olamide has attracted ladies finer than my mom,…     Jonathan condoles with Murray-Bruce over mother’s death   noblejunioruchenna wrote: “No be wizkid inspire you abeg Na terry g fkaywise asked: “Na portable type “inspired?” @hexbeewhy tweeted: “Wizkid ojuelegba no inspire u anything. No dey lie.” @ideyfindbabe said: “Wetin you talk? why everybody con dey lie like this una go just dey lie sey Na WIZ inspire una…… Oya sing one Big Wiz song.” @Iammikey9 wrote: “Ur music sounds as if u ar inspired by terry G rosythrone stated: “Abeg not my WizKid, the both music gat no connections biko.” maleekpholly_ quizzed: “Na portable write that thing?” official__osebliz wrote: “Wizkid don suffer.”